oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Produce 1893
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Edwin Best
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Greenback (Tenn.); Produce trade;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of Joseph Scott and John Wear heading to Sweetwater to sell a load of produce. On December. 6, 1893, The Maryville Times reported, "Messrs. Joe Scott and John Ware are doing a lively business peddling, the proceeds of last week being near $200."
